properties.abstract: Ravines and wooded knolls characterize fir-cone country, pilgrims stop at the Fischingen Benedictine Monastery. Steep Sternenberg rewards with panoramic views. Over flat marshland at the Pfffikersee, through villages and farm fields down to Zrichsee.
properties.description:
Start in Konstanz, historic city on the Bodensee, following the Schwabenweg path up the Seercken hills, in the tranquillity of the Bommer ponds. Past the Ottenberg vineyards to Weinfelden and a refreshment in the early baroque Gasthaus zum Trauben.

You then cross the Thur, pedal over the Oppikon plateau, gentle valleys become ravines, you are in fir-cone country. Then you pass the Fischingen Benedictine Monastery. Steep wooded knolls in Tssberg country, grandiose views in Sternenberg. Looms have long ceased to clatter on the Tss.

Bordered by reeds and blossoming marshland, the Pfffikersee in flat countryside, residential areas compete with farming, the Pfannenstiel still blocks open views of the Zrichsee, which soon is revealed in its entire length.
properties.title: Pilger-Route
